ton, for example in Cumbria, Greater London (formerly in Kent), Hampshire, Lincolnshire, Wiltshire, and Yorkshire. Most of these are named from Old English <i>croft</i> ‘paddock, vegetable garden’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’, but the one in Greater London probably has as its first element Old English <i>cropp</i> ‘swelling, mound’ (compare   Cropper  ) and that in Lincolnshire Old English <i>croh</i> ‘saffron’ (from Latin <i>crocus</i>).","History: A family called Crofton was established in Ireland by John Crofton (died 1610), who held high office under Elizabeth I and acquired vast estates when he accompanied Sir Henry Sidney, Lord Deputy, into Ireland in 1565."],"variants":[{"name":"Cropper","meanings":["English (mainly Lancashire): occupational name for a picker of fruit or vegetables or a reaper of cereal crops, from <i>cropper(e)</i> ‘one who reaps crops or trims trees’, an agent derivative of Middle English <i>cropt(en)</i> ‘to pick’. The word was used also to denote the polling of livestock and the name may therefore have been given to someone with this responsibility."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":22,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":31,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":66,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":97,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine of Crofton was born about 1193, in Thursby, Cumberland, England. She had at least 1 son with Stephen de Crofton."},"et":{"about 1193–":"umbes 1193–Surnud","1189–Male":"1189–Surnud","1216–Male":"1216–Surnud","1193–Female":"1193–Surnud","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1193":"umbes 1193","1224":"1224","1189":"1189","1193":"1193","1290":"1290","Thursby Saint Andrew's, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, England","Thursby, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"about 1193–":"noin 1193–Kuollut","1189–Male":"1189–Kuollut","1216–Male":"1216–Kuollut","1193–Female":"1193–Kuollut","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1193":"noin 1193","1224":"1224","1189":"1189","1193":"1193","1290":"1290","Thursby Saint Andrew's, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, England","Thursby, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, England"},"fr":{"about 1193–":"environ 1193–Décédée","1189–Male":"1189–Décédé","1216–Male":"1216–Décédé","1193–Female":"1193–Décédée","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1193":"environ 1193","1224":"1224","1189":"1189","1193":"1193","1290":"1290","Thursby Saint Andrew's, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, Angleterre","Thursby, Allerdale district, Cumberland, England":"Thursby, Cumberland, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Katherine of Crofton est née envi